abstract: MLB Roundup; Chicago Cubs and Cincinnati Reds split doubleheader, with Reds winning opener, 9-1, and Cubs taking second game, 6-5; other baseball scores noted.
lead_paragraph: Taylor Teagarden singled home the tiebreaking run with two outs in the ninth inning, completing the Chicago Cubs’ biggest comeback of the season.

headline.main: Cubs Overcome 5-0 Deficit and Salvage Split With Reds
headline.print_headline: Cubs Overcome 5-0 Deficit and Salvage Split With Reds
